<div id="review_3580302051" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3580302051" />
    <a title="Vicki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8620411-vicki"><img alt="Vicki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1334035698p2/8620411.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3580302051?book_show_action=true">Oct 11, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vicki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vicki" href="/user/show/8620411-vicki">Vicki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=101-200-pages">101-200-pages</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=audio-book">audio-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=urban-fantasy">urban-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8620411-vicki?shelf=vampires">vampires</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3580302051" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6941906160692690211">Paranormal Romance is not my favorite read, but I liked this one all right. I didn&apos;t love it though. The audience this book is written for is young adults. Zoe is the teenage female MC whose mother has terminal cancer. As one can only imagine it turns her world upside down. As anyone can tell you if you&apos;ve ever gone through something like this, it can be a very lonely place for the loved ones of the ill. In comes Simon the vampire, which of course she doesn&apos;t realize. But he does fill a void. I </span>
  <span id="freeText6941906160692690211" style="display:none">Paranormal Romance is not my favorite read, but I liked this one all right. I didn't love it though. The audience this book is written for is young adults. Zoe is the teenage female MC whose mother has terminal cancer. As one can only imagine it turns her world upside down. As anyone can tell you if you've ever gone through something like this, it can be a very lonely place for the loved ones of the ill. In comes Simon the vampire, which of course she doesn't realize. But he does fill a void. I think young adults would especially enjoy this one since there is romance between a vampire and human and the unknown can be exciting to young people. I found it intriguing that Simon has his own issues dealing with a variety of emotions. Loneliness is an obvious subject in the story of Zoe and Simon and I thought Klause did a good job showing how anyone, anywhere, can be lonely. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6941906160692690211" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3580302051">
  <td colspan="2">
