        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer27073906" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1649830321295059153">The first of it&apos;s kind -- a teen vampire love story. In that respect I did like the story, the concepts were intriguing and an easy story to follow. I did find it quite dated however, very 90s lit. The author also seemed like she was a teen herself in some respects..the story felt a little young and undeveloped. <br/><br/>Some things that bothered me: Zoe is basically anorexic, but no one really says anything about it. Her mother is dying and she is trying to accept death with the help of Simon, the tortu</span>
  <span id="freeText1649830321295059153" style="display:none">The first of it's kind -- a teen vampire love story. In that respect I did like the story, the concepts were intriguing and an easy story to follow. I did find it quite dated however, very 90s lit. The author also seemed like she was a teen herself in some respects..the story felt a little young and undeveloped. <br /><br />Some things that bothered me: Zoe is basically anorexic, but no one really says anything about it. Her mother is dying and she is trying to accept death with the help of Simon, the tortured vampire. I'm happy to say most teen writers have moved away from sappy stories like this. So it was okay, but not so inspiring now.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1649830321295059153" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

