<div id="review_2596432659" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2596432659" />
    <a title="Hannah Timm" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71452305-hannah-timm"><img alt="Hannah Timm" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2596432659?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hannah Timm" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hannah Timm" href="/user/show/71452305-hannah-timm">Hannah Timm</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2596432659" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9680805338314484521">Book title: <i>The Silver Kiss</i><br/><br/>Personal Response:<br/>Overall, I really liked <i>The Silver Kiss </i>. I really liked the dark and broodiness, but also the cute romance. I found it upsetting that Zoe and Simon built up their relationship only for Simon to willingly go to Heaven. However, I liked how the author uses Simon to bring out Zoeâs complex character and helps her move on with her problems along with his problem. Also, I like how Simonâs dark character brings out light in Zoeâs depressed character. Overa</span>
  <span id="freeText9680805338314484521" style="display:none">Book title: <i>The Silver Kiss</i><br /><br />Personal Response:<br />Overall, I really liked <i>The Silver Kiss </i>. I really liked the dark and broodiness, but also the cute romance. I found it upsetting that Zoe and Simon built up their relationship only for Simon to willingly go to Heaven. However, I liked how the author uses Simon to bring out Zoeâs complex character and helps her move on with her problems along with his problem. Also, I like how Simonâs dark character brings out light in Zoeâs depressed character. Overall, I really liked this book.<br /><br />Plot Summary:<br />Zoe is a 16-year-old in a rough situation. Her mother is dying from cancer, her father is ignoring her for her mother, and her best friend and neighbor is moving away. Her life is crashing on her and she feels alone and desperate. She then becomes confused when she meets an odd boy named Simon. She doesnât know what to make of him. They meet at night and they talk and get comfortable with each other but something is odd about Simon. One day she catches him all bloody in the ally after a murder. He then explains to her that the murders are by his brother who is feeding off of people and then slashing their necks. He and his brother, Christopher, are vampires. Simon has been chasing his murderous older, child brother for centuries, trying to stop him and then go to Heaven. After learning this they continue to talk. She is drawn to him by empathy and fear. She also distracts herself from her mother's fatal illness by helping Simon defeat Christopher. They set up a trap to kill Christopher. Christopher caches Simon but does not expect Zoe. As Christopher goes in to kill Zoe, she crucifies him with a cross and the Simon kills him with a stake. With Christopher dead, Simon feels free to move on. He says his goodbye to Zoe and Zoe is left alone once again, but this time with confidence.<br /><br />Characterization:<br />In this book, Zoe had a significant role. She is only a 16 year old going through terrible situations of her mother dying and loneliness. She was isolated by grief, anger, and fear. But when she meets Simon a light begins to grow. Her development from a depressed lonely teenage girl, to a romantic vampire slayer, is a lot of development. She mourns and acknowledges her losses but she moves on. That is a huge development for a person.<br /><br />Recommendation:<br />I would recommend this book to anyone interested in fantasies. If you like vampires, death, romance, or overall drama, this book is for you. It is a good 2 in 1 book with mystery and romance. I recommend this book to high school vampire nerds.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9680805338314484521" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


