<div id="review_2072573402" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2072573402" />
    <a title="Biana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13595244-biana"><img alt="Biana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1550519916p2/13595244.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2072573402?book_show_action=true">Jul 31, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Biana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Biana" href="/user/show/13595244-biana">Biana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8941979-the-silver-kiss">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13595244-biana?shelf=quit-before-the-end">quit-before-the-end</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13595244-biana?shelf=2017">2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2072573402" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14193376756069298158">Sometimes I feel like I can&apos;t truly judge a book unless I finish the book. And then I read another couple pages and I remind myself that life is too short to read bad books. I did this back and forth through 66% of this book. And I&apos;m done now.<br/><br/>I gave it such a low rating because not only was it cliche vampire romance, it was HEAVY handed. Pages and pages were dedicated to our character&apos;s emotions about her mother dying and her father ignoring her. But really that just set her up to be home alone </span>
  <span id="freeText14193376756069298158" style="display:none">Sometimes I feel like I can't truly judge a book unless I finish the book. And then I read another couple pages and I remind myself that life is too short to read bad books. I did this back and forth through 66% of this book. And I'm done now.<br /><br />I gave it such a low rating because not only was it cliche vampire romance, it was HEAVY handed. Pages and pages were dedicated to our character's emotions about her mother dying and her father ignoring her. But really that just set her up to be home alone with the handsome, rakish, sensitive soul mate of a vampire came and revealed himself to her. *eyeroll*<br /><br />Then there is HIS story, how and why he's a vampire. Meh, that was okay. But he's after a BAD vampire. And he can turn to mist. And he had a pet cat. Tell me...how is that better than sparkling? Just saying...there are differences, it's not a cut and paste from the vampire genre, but it's also nothing original. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14193376756069298158" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


